ISR08999 | COS Practicm-Methodology | https://enr-apps.as.cmu.edu/open/SOC/SOCServlet/courseDetails?COURSE=08999&SEMESTER=F15 | instructors:Carley, Kathleen description:08-999:  Any Ph.D. or Master's student is allowed to register.  Undergraduates  with permission of Instructor.    This course provides an overview of research in the COS area. Students  learn about the breadth of research, core theories, and applicable  methods in this highly inter- and multi-disciplinary area.  Students do a project in this area with associated presentations and written material.      All first year COS students are required to that this course.  This  course is offered in the fall semester only.  All COS students are required to  get a grade of B or better.
